the lublin regional assembly (polish: sejmik województwa lubelskiego) is the regional legislature of the voivodeship of lublin in poland. it is a unicameral parliamentary body consisting of thirty-three councillors chosen during regional elections for a four-year term. the current chairperson of the assembly is przemysław litwiniuk. the assembly elects the executive board that acts as the collective executive for the provincial government, headed by the voivodeship marshal. the current executive board of lublin is a coalition government between the polish people's party and civic platform under the leadership of marshal sławomir sosnowski of the psl. the assembly meets within the marshal's office in the capital city of lublin.